      <div>
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-furdu-muted mb-3">Workflow &amp; Event Terms</p>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-3">
          {([
            {
              term: 'Pass',
              def: 'A short, time-boxed visit to a non-primary event (typically 15–30 min). The shooter drops in, captures key frames, then moves on — full-event coverage is not required.',
            },
            {
              term: 'Primary event (⭐)',
              def: 'A high-priority event requiring continuous full coverage for its entire duration. At least one shooter must be present from start to finish, no exceptions.',
            },
            {
              term: 'Assigned event',
              def: 'A coverage target in your schedule — not a mandatory full-duration commitment. Shoot until you meet the quota, capture highlights, and have a good set of shots. Once satisfied, you can roam and explore the con until your next assignment. Just be back on location before the next scheduled block.',
            },
            {
              term: 'Solo window',
              def: 'A scheduled block where only one photographer covers an event — because the other is offloading, on a pass, or on break.',
            },
            {
              term: 'Offload window',
              def: 'A scheduled gap in programming where one or both shooters head to ConOps to transfer files from their active card to the server.',
            },
            {
              term: 'Staggered offload',
              def: 'Jarrod offloads first at a DJ transition or event gap, then Neon offloads 15 min later — ensuring at least one shooter stays on the floor at all times.',
            },
            {
              term: 'Wrap offload',
              def: 'The final end-of-night offload after the last shooting block. All remaining cards are transferred before both shooters finish for the day.',
            },
            {
              term: 'Card rotation',
              def: 'The two-card system: one card is active in-camera, one is in-pocket as the swap. At each offload window, swap cards so the camera is ready immediately while the full card is offloaded.',
            },
            {
              term: 'Culling',
              def: "Post-shoot selection process: unusable, blurry, duplicate, or otherwise reject shots are flagged and removed before editing begins. Reo's task — do not pre-cull before uploading.",
